The paper deals with solving combined satisfiability problems that involve both traditional clauses and parity constraints. This is a topic that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), data structures (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on the use of SAT solvers and xor-reasoning, which are more commonly associated with logic and cryptography, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LO and cs.CR.
